					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>153 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>340</height>
										<width>227</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>230</height>
										<width>145/150</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>153 folios (+ 4 unfoliated flyleaves at the beginning and 2 at the end). Folios 1 and 2 are paper flyleaves.</p>
									<p>Irregular Hebrew foliation (92-159), 91 leaves might be missing at the beginning and 8 leaves missing after folio 66.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of 8 leaves each, marked with a vertical catchword at the end.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stains and tidemarks from damp, especially on first and last few leaves.</p>
									<p>Slight rodent damage at bottom corner in part.</p>
									<p>Ink blurred in parts.</p>
									<p>Foredge of paper ends rolling. Small tears.</p>
									<p>Lacuna after folio 132.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="36 38" writtenLines="36 38">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Regular layout with hard point ruling. Last written line outside ruling.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking.</p>
									<p>Titles and initial words given in large square characters.</p>
									<p>Occasional infralinear vocalization.</p>
									<p>Marginal notes and additions, in various hands.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square script of the 14th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Mosheh</name>: his name marked off frequently in the text, e.g., folio 8v, 14v, etc.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
